en_179899_0	The Election Commission says that displaying of cut-outs and posters using politicians’ images is against election law.
en_179899_1	Police media spokesperson SP Ruwan Gunasekara said that action would be taken against candidates engaging in propaganda using their images.
en_179899_2	Similarly, a candidate could display in his party office only his photograph and his political party leader’s image.
en_179899_3	Additional Election Commissioner Saman Sri Ratnayake told our news team that action would be taken regarding the display of cut-outs and posters illegally using candidates’ and politicians’ images.
